attributeList.attribute: Whetstine JR., Nottke A., Lan F., Huarte M., Smolikov S., Chen Z., Spooner E., Li E., Zhang G., Colaiacovo M., Shi Y.
Demethylation reaction was carried out using full-length JMJD2A and calf thymus histone fraction II-A.

In the presence of H188A the trimethyllysine 9 and 36 antibodies colocalise with the HA antibodies. On overexpression of the HA-JMJD2A protein there is decrease in presence of methylated H3K9 and H3K36 suggesting a demethylase activity.

A mixture of histones purified from calf thymus (Sigma) were used. Two histone H3 proteins from bovin origin present in UniProtKB-SwissProt P68432 and P84227. These have identical aminoacid sequences.
Interaction results in demethylation of the trimethyllysine.
Antibodies against H3K9Me3 and H3K36Me3 were used.
